Back to Puzzle

1998 Chung, Forsyth JIGSAW PUZZLE SOLVER USING SHAPE AND COLOR
PDF -- Finds four corners of each piece.
2002 Goldberg A Global Approach to Automatic Solution of Jigsaw Puzzles
PDF -- finds indents and outdents
2003 Yao A shape and image merging technique to solve jigsaw puzzles
PDF -- nice history of computer vision solutions to the jigsaw puzzle problem nice pictures of reconstruction challenges This guy had been working on the jigsaw problem for at least 6 years before publishing this paper - his first publication on this topic was in 1997, he also has a 2002 paper that deals with puzzle piece extraction and corner detection
2004 DeBock CONSTRUCTING THE TOPOLOGICAL SOLUTION OF JIGSAW PUZZLES
PDF -- this guy did his masters thesis on computer vision and jigsaw puzzles he seems to be one of the first to do non-canonical work, but I cant seem to find the paper cited by many after him called "Computer Vision Techniques for Semiautomatic Reconstruction of Ripped-up Documents." Here is his home page -you can view his thesis here too http://telin.ugent.be/~jdebock/
2006 Makridis A NEW TECHNIQUE FOR SOLVING A JIGSAW PUZZLE
PDF -- non-canonical jigsaw puzzles
2006 Zhu A Partial Curve Matching Method for Automatic Reassembly of 2D Fragments
PDF -- non-canonical - ripped up document






